WEBVTT

00:32.597 --> 00:33.990
[sneezes]

00:42.781 --> 00:45.436
[vocalizes fanfare]

00:45.480 --> 00:47.569
["The Other Side" by SZA
and Justin Timberlake playing]

00:47.612 --> 00:50.093
CLOUD GUY: Once upon a time,
there were two Trolls.

00:50.137 --> 00:52.226
-One was named Poppy.
-Hey. How's it going?

00:52.269 --> 00:53.792
CLOUD GUY:
The other was named Branch.

00:53.836 --> 00:55.011
What's up?

00:55.055 --> 00:56.795
CLOUD GUY: Together, they saved the world.

00:56.839 --> 00:58.275
TROLLS:
Hooray!

00:58.319 --> 00:59.798
CLOUD GUY:
Poppy became queen.

00:59.842 --> 01:01.365
Branch found his true colors.

01:01.409 --> 01:03.628
And the two of them
became best friends.

01:03.672 --> 01:05.761
[imitates fireworks popping]

01:05.804 --> 01:06.762
Boom.

01:06.805 --> 01:07.937
And that was that.

01:07.980 --> 01:09.982
Pretty cute, right?
Not to me.

01:10.026 --> 01:12.637
I'm the type of cloud
that goes for...

01:12.681 --> 01:13.856
this sorta thang.

01:13.899 --> 01:15.292
[dogs barking, yapping]

01:15.336 --> 01:16.554
Mm.

01:16.598 --> 01:18.600
Anyhoo, what Poppy and Branch
didn't know

01:18.643 --> 01:21.733
is that their world was
a lot bigger than they knew.

01:21.777 --> 01:25.476
Like, a lot, lot, lot,
lot bigger!

01:25.520 --> 01:28.305
[whooshing]

01:28.349 --> 01:31.091
-[water burbling]
-[ocean creatures calling]

01:33.658 --> 01:35.878
[heartbeat thumping]

01:39.664 --> 01:41.623
[crowd cheering faintly
in distance]

01:41.666 --> 01:43.407
["One More Time"
playing in distance]

01:43.451 --> 01:45.888
[cheering and electronic
dance music growing louder]

01:51.415 --> 01:52.547
[music playing loudly]

01:52.590 --> 01:54.636
♪ One more time

01:54.679 --> 01:55.898
♪ One more time,
one more time ♪

01:55.941 --> 01:59.119
What's up, my techno Trolls?!

01:59.162 --> 02:00.729
-[crowd cheering]
-♪ One more time

02:00.772 --> 02:02.557
-♪ One more time
-Yeah!

02:02.600 --> 02:04.254
♪ We're gonna celebrate

02:04.298 --> 02:08.258
♪ Oh, yeah, all right,
don't stop the dancing ♪

02:08.302 --> 02:12.523
Tonight is about family,
love and music!

02:12.567 --> 02:14.090
[crowd cheering]

02:14.134 --> 02:14.917
Come on!

02:14.960 --> 02:17.354
Let me see you jump!

02:17.398 --> 02:19.400
One, two, three, four!

02:20.401 --> 02:22.664
And get ready for the drop!

02:22.707 --> 02:24.187
Are you ready, little buddy?

02:24.231 --> 02:26.015
Let's do this, King Trollex!

02:26.058 --> 02:27.799
-Wait for it!
-[beat building]

02:27.843 --> 02:29.410
Come on.

02:29.453 --> 02:30.541
Wait for it.

02:30.585 --> 02:31.629
Yes.

02:31.673 --> 02:34.284
-Wait for it.
-Wait for it!

02:34.328 --> 02:35.981
Wait for it.

02:36.025 --> 02:37.505
Come on, man, hit me!

02:37.548 --> 02:39.594
Just do it already!

02:39.637 --> 02:41.900
[beat building loudly]

02:41.944 --> 02:43.206
-♪ One more time
-[beat drops]

02:43.250 --> 02:45.774
♪ Music's got me feeling
so free ♪

02:45.817 --> 02:47.036
-[sighs]
-♪ We're gonna celebrate

02:47.079 --> 02:48.559
-Oh, yeah! -♪ Celebrate
and dance so free ♪

02:48.603 --> 02:51.736
-♪ Gonna party all night
-♪ One more time

02:51.780 --> 02:54.391
♪ One more time,
we're gonna celebrate ♪

02:54.435 --> 02:56.872
♪ Oh, yeah, all right,
don't stop the dancing ♪

02:56.915 --> 03:00.223
-♪ Don't stop the dancing
-♪ Oh, yeah, all right

03:00.267 --> 03:01.790
-♪ Don't stop the...
-[laughs] -[music stops]

03:01.833 --> 03:03.139
[crowd groaning]

03:03.183 --> 03:04.358
Don't worry, everybody.

03:04.401 --> 03:05.620
We'll get back to the party
in a minute.

03:05.663 --> 03:08.231
Let me just take care
of this real quick.

03:08.275 --> 03:11.191
♪

03:16.500 --> 03:18.502
[electrical buzzing]

03:21.636 --> 03:23.290
BARB:
Hey, man.

03:23.333 --> 03:24.508
There he is!

03:24.552 --> 03:27.381
King Trollex of
the Techno Trolls, right?

03:27.424 --> 03:29.470
That's right.
Who's asking?

03:29.513 --> 03:30.906
Queen Barb.

03:30.949 --> 03:32.864
Of the Hard Rock Trolls.

03:34.257 --> 03:36.564
And I'm here to take
your string, bro.

03:36.607 --> 03:39.219
[plays loud ascending chord]

03:41.221 --> 03:42.047
No way.

03:42.091 --> 03:44.006
Ooh, don't do it, man.

03:44.049 --> 03:47.183
If we lose our string,
we lose our music.

03:48.315 --> 03:50.142
You mean your bleeps
and bloops?

03:50.186 --> 03:52.449
Beep, beep, beep,
beep-beep, boo.

03:52.493 --> 03:54.364
[chuckles]:
Yeah. That's not music.

03:54.408 --> 03:57.019
Do you want to hear
some real music?

03:57.846 --> 03:58.977
Rockers!

03:59.021 --> 04:01.415
[frightened murmuring]

04:01.458 --> 04:03.460
[electrical buzzing]

04:08.857 --> 04:10.206
Ah!

04:13.340 --> 04:17.126
