♪ Fun.

08:10.359 --> 08:11.621
[Trolls murmuring happily]

08:11.665 --> 08:13.884
Hey! That was some
fancy footwork, Cooper.

08:13.928 --> 08:15.277
Some people just got it.

08:15.320 --> 08:18.236
Biggie, Mr. Dinkles,
you two were on fire!

08:18.280 --> 08:20.021
Yeah, sorry about that,
Queen Poppy.

08:20.064 --> 08:21.718
[squeaks]

08:21.762 --> 08:24.068
I'm digging
that new anklet, Legsly.

08:24.112 --> 08:25.505
Thanks, Poppy.

08:25.548 --> 08:29.030
Kisses and donuts
and sprinkles!

08:29.073 --> 08:30.640
Ah, what a Troll.

08:30.684 --> 08:34.296
Tiny Diamond, welcome
to the family, little buddy.

08:34.339 --> 08:35.645
Thanks, Aunt Poppy.

08:35.689 --> 08:37.473
And thanks to this
silver-haired daddy of mine

08:37.517 --> 08:39.083
for bringing me
into this world.

08:39.127 --> 08:40.694
Oh.

08:40.737 --> 08:42.870
I never knew my heart
could be so full.

08:42.913 --> 08:44.436
Peace and love.
Bless up.

08:44.480 --> 08:46.134
Tiny and Daddy out.

08:46.177 --> 08:48.528
Oh. Okay, bye.

08:49.703 --> 08:51.356
Hey, uh, Poppy,

08:51.400 --> 08:53.750
there's something
I was hoping to ask you.

08:53.794 --> 08:55.447
I-I mean,
I guess it's something

08:55.491 --> 08:58.363
I want to tell you, more so.

08:58.407 --> 08:59.669
-Uh-huh.
-Uh, but listen.

08:59.713 --> 09:03.064
You could feel free
to respond to it,

09:03.107 --> 09:05.806
uh, with an answer,
i-if you wanted.

09:05.849 --> 09:07.068
Sure. What's up?

09:07.111 --> 09:10.898
Uh, what's up is I, uh,

09:10.941 --> 09:13.378
I-I-I-I-I-I...

09:13.422 --> 09:15.772
I wanted to tell you that...

09:17.600 --> 09:18.558
Uh...

09:18.601 --> 09:19.907
[groans]

09:21.343 --> 09:23.911
You're crushing it
at this queen thing.

09:23.954 --> 09:25.782
Aw, Branch, thank you.

09:25.826 --> 09:27.044
Being a good queen is

09:27.088 --> 09:29.481
the most important thing
in the world to me.

09:29.525 --> 09:30.961
Other than being your friend.

09:31.005 --> 09:33.355
[echoing]: Friend, friend, friend, friend,

09:33.398 --> 09:35.618
friend, friend, friend.

09:35.662 --> 09:37.664
Uh, five it up?

09:37.707 --> 09:40.318
Huh. That could've been better.
Let's try that again.

09:41.058 --> 09:43.104
O-Okay, one more.

09:43.147 --> 09:45.628
Huh. For some reason, we can't
seem to make a good connection.

09:45.672 --> 09:47.935
-[Poppy chuckles, Branch sighs]
-[Fuzzbert babbling]

09:47.978 --> 09:49.414
Oh, yes, Fuzzbert!

09:49.458 --> 09:51.591
-Now, that's a good connection.
-[groans]

09:51.634 --> 09:53.157
BIGGIE:
[screams] Poppy, help!

09:53.201 --> 09:54.289
-Ooh.
-Poppy!

09:54.332 --> 09:56.465
-[shrieking, gasping]
-[wild grunting]

09:57.945 --> 09:58.989
Watch it, watch it!

09:59.033 --> 10:00.730
-Biggie?
-TROLL: Oh, run!

10:00.774 --> 10:02.732
-[Trolls clamoring]
-[Biggie screams]

10:02.776 --> 10:03.994
Help!

10:04.038 --> 10:06.170
I'm being harangued
by a monster! [gasps]

10:06.214 --> 10:08.956
-Someone stop it! [shrieks]
-[wild grunting continues]

10:10.697 --> 10:12.960
Gotcha! Ah! It's in my hair!
It's in my hair!

10:13.003 --> 10:15.049
-Get it out, get it out,
get it out! -[Branch yells]

10:15.092 --> 10:17.181
[shushing]

10:17.225 --> 10:18.356
There you go.

10:18.400 --> 10:21.011
-[eyes boinging]
-[purring]

10:21.055 --> 10:22.447
There you go. Calm down.

10:22.491 --> 10:23.971
Who's a good boy?

10:24.014 --> 10:25.233
What is that thing?

10:25.276 --> 10:26.364
It's creepy.

10:26.408 --> 10:27.539
BOTH:
It's scary.

10:27.583 --> 10:29.890
[auto-tuned]:
And nasty.

10:29.933 --> 10:32.240
-Hold me, Daddy.
-Oh.

10:36.374 --> 10:38.768
"To Queen Poppy."

10:38.812 --> 10:40.117
[Trolls gasp]

10:40.161 --> 10:41.684
Oh, don't worry, everyone.

10:41.728 --> 10:43.555
It looks like
it's just an invitation.

10:43.599 --> 10:44.992
-Whew!
-[relieved murmuring, sighing]

10:45.035 --> 10:46.341
Just an invitation.

10:46.384 --> 10:47.908
-COOPER: I love invitations.
-[clears throat]

10:47.951 --> 10:49.692
"Barb, the Queen of Rock,

10:49.736 --> 10:53.827
"announces her One Nation
Under Rock World Tour.

10:53.870 --> 10:55.480
"Bring your string
to the biggest party

10:55.524 --> 10:56.786
the world has ever seen."

10:56.830 --> 10:58.919
-Queen of Rock?
-KING PEPPY: It's nothing!

10:58.962 --> 11:01.704
It means nothing at all.
It's just junk mail.

11:01.748 --> 11:02.879
You don't need
to worry about it.

11:02.923 --> 11:04.185
I mean, quit looking at it,
everyone.

11:04.228 --> 11:05.839
Forget what you saw!

11:05.882 --> 11:07.101
[chewing noisily]

11:07.144 --> 11:08.189
[Branch yells]

11:08.232 --> 11:10.060
-[grunting]
-[shushing]

11:10.104 --> 11:11.714
-There you go. There you go.
-[eyes boinging]

11:11.758 --> 11:14.108
-Calm down. Calm down.
-[purring]

11:14.151 --> 11:15.849
[quietly]:
There you go.

11:16.893 --> 11:19.113
Okay, I'm calm.

11:19.156 --> 11:20.114
I'm calm.

11:20.157 --> 11:22.333
Dad, what's going on?

11:22.377 --> 11:25.641
Well, I have long feared
this day would come.

11:25.685 --> 11:28.775
I was hoping to protect you
from this, Poppy.

11:28.818 --> 11:29.863
Protect me?

11:29.906 --> 11:31.255
I'm not a little kid
anymore, Dad.

11:31.299 --> 11:32.648
I'm the queen now.

11:33.475 --> 11:35.782
You're right.

11:35.825 --> 11:40.787
The truth is we are not alone
in this world.

11:40.830 --> 11:43.485
[eerie warbling]

11:43.528 --> 11:45.226
-[warbling stops]
-[stammers, shushes]

11:45.269 --> 11:47.750
There are other kinds
of Trolls.

11:47.794 --> 11:49.578
-TROLL: What?
-Wow. That's...

11:49.621 --> 11:50.666
Dad, that's great.

11:50.710 --> 11:52.537
The more Trolls, the merrier.

11:52.581 --> 11:54.191
You don't understand.

11:54.235 --> 11:56.237
These other Trolls
aren't like us.

11:56.280 --> 11:58.239
They're different.

11:58.282 --> 11:59.936
Different how?

11:59.980 --> 12:01.068
Different like Legsly?

12:01.111 --> 12:02.460
I love being me.

12:02.504 --> 12:03.940
-Or Fuzzbert? Or Smidge?
-[Fuzzbert babbling]

12:03.984 --> 12:05.028
Or Skyscraper Troll?

12:05.072 --> 12:07.117
[in unison]:
Yeah, different like me?

12:07.161 --> 12:08.728
No, it's not that.

12:08.771 --> 12:11.774
They're different in ways
you can't even imagine.

12:11.818 --> 12:13.950
-[vocalizing pop music]
-You see, we love music

12:13.994 --> 12:16.387
with a hummable hook,
with an upbeat melody,

12:16.431 --> 12:19.347
with a catchy rhythm that makes
you want to snap your fingers,

12:19.390 --> 12:21.828
tap your toes
and wiggle your butt.

12:21.871 --> 12:22.872
That's our music.

12:22.916 --> 12:25.701
That's what makes us
Pop Trolls.

12:25.745 --> 12:27.398
-Ooh.
-It is. -Yes.

12:27.442 --> 12:29.792
But these other Trolls,
they sing different.

12:29.836 --> 12:31.098
-[gasping]
-They dance different.

12:31.141 --> 12:33.578
Why, some of them
can't even begin to grasp

12:33.622 --> 12:36.190
the concept of Hammer Time.

12:36.233 --> 12:38.540
["U Can't Touch This" playing]

12:38.583 --> 12:40.107
You can't touch that!

12:40.150 --> 12:41.151
[screaming]

12:41.195 --> 12:43.371
[Trolls clamoring]

12:43.414 --> 12:45.460
-[crying]
-[crying]

12:45.503 --> 12:46.722
[screaming]

12:46.766 --> 12:48.680
-♪ Stop.
-[music and clamoring stop]

12:49.812 --> 12:53.076
How about we break down
to a smaller group?

12:53.120 --> 12:55.122
[birds chirping]

12:57.167 --> 13:00.475
It's a story as old as time.

13:00.518 --> 13:01.737
[clears throat]

13:01.781 --> 13:04.696
In the beginning,
there was silence.

13:07.264 --> 13:08.875
[singsongy]:
Boring.

13:08.918 --> 13:11.399
KING PEPPY: Until one day,
someone made a sound.

13:11.442 --> 13:12.966
-[plays note]
-[Trolls oohing]

13:13.009 --> 13:15.882
Our ancestors were
so inspired by the sound,

13:15.925 --> 13:18.406
-they took six strings.
-[melody plays]

13:18.449 --> 13:23.150
And those six strings had the power to control all music.

13:23.193 --> 13:24.542
They could play anything.

13:24.586 --> 13:26.196
[harp strumming]

13:26.240 --> 13:28.329
-[different styles playing]
-Techno, funk, classical,

13:28.372 --> 13:30.897
country, hard rock and pop.

13:30.940 --> 13:33.682
And every kind of music
in between.

13:33.725 --> 13:35.423
There was something
for everyone.

13:35.466 --> 13:37.120
It was one big party.

13:37.164 --> 13:38.469
TROLLS:
Yay!

13:38.513 --> 13:40.036
KING PEPPY:
But little by little,

13:40.080 --> 13:42.560
Trolls became intolerant
of each other's music.

13:42.604 --> 13:43.866
-[Trolls arguing]
-TROLL: I want it!

13:43.910 --> 13:46.086
-I want to listen to techno!
-No fair!

13:46.129 --> 13:47.870
Hey, y'all, I want country.

13:47.914 --> 13:50.264
KING PEPPY: They fought
over what kind of music

13:50.307 --> 13:51.874
the strings would play.

13:51.918 --> 13:54.529
The elders realized
there was but one solution.

13:54.572 --> 13:56.748
TROLLS: Blah,
blah-blah-blah-blah. Agreed.

13:56.792 --> 13:59.273
KING PEPPY:
Each tribe would take a string

13:59.316 --> 14:01.753
-and go their separate ways.
-[Trolls chattering]

14:03.364 --> 14:07.498
Those six tribes have lived
in isolation ever since.

14:07.542 --> 14:10.284
Techno, Country, Rock,

14:10.327 --> 14:12.286
Classical, Funk,

14:12.329 --> 14:15.115
and us, the Pop Trolls.

14:16.290 --> 14:18.596
Now Barb's announcement
makes sense.

14:18.640 --> 14:20.076
She wants to reunite
the strings

14:20.120 --> 14:22.818
so the Troll World
can be one big party again.

14:22.862 --> 14:24.341
Wait, that's all you heard?

14:24.385 --> 14:26.126
-One big party?
-[chuckles]: Yeah!

14:26.169 --> 14:28.084
It's when all the Trolls
lived in harmony.

14:28.128 --> 14:30.565
And what's more important
than living in harmony?

14:30.608 --> 14:31.871
Well, I heard fighting.

14:31.914 --> 14:33.350
The strings together
leads to fighting.

14:33.394 --> 14:34.656
KING PEPPY:
Exactly, Branch.

14:34.699 --> 14:37.354
That's why we need
to keep our string safe.

14:37.398 --> 14:39.617
♪

14:43.273 --> 14:44.274
Behold!

14:44.318 --> 14:47.016
The pop music string.

14:47.060 --> 14:50.019
FEMALE STRING VOICE:
♪ Oh, yeah.

14:50.063 --> 14:52.500
-[Trolls gasping]
-[magic jingling]

14:55.111 --> 14:56.939
It's beautiful.

14:56.983 --> 14:58.506
KING PEPPY:
And powerful.

14:58.549 --> 15:01.901
Which is why we can't let it
fall into the wrong hands.

15:01.944 --> 15:04.251
And we won't.
Not on my watch.

15:04.294 --> 15:06.644
What we need is a plan.

15:06.688 --> 15:07.907
Don't worry.

15:07.950 --> 15:10.997
I've been preparing
for this day for years.

15:11.040 --> 15:12.476
-We run.
-Run?

15:12.520 --> 15:13.477
And hide.

15:13.521 --> 15:15.088
On it.

15:15.131 --> 15:18.178
But we don't even know what
we're running and hiding from.

15:18.221 --> 15:21.833
We're hiding from Barb and
all the other different Trolls.

15:21.877 --> 15:23.661
POPPY:
You're assuming the worst about

15:23.705 --> 15:25.228
someone you haven't even met.

15:25.272 --> 15:28.579
-You're not listening to me.
-You're not listening to me.

15:28.623 --> 15:31.365
-I'm your father!
-And I'm the queen.

15:31.408 --> 15:32.975
Uh, father trumps queen.

15:33.019 --> 15:35.673
Now, there's no time
to debate this. Let's go.

15:35.717 --> 15:37.414
Come along, Branch.

15:37.458 --> 15:39.199
Well, I, um...

15:40.243 --> 15:42.419
We're all Trolls.

15:42.463 --> 15:44.682
Differences don't matter.

15:45.596 --> 15:46.858
[growling]

15:46.902 --> 15:48.860
Oh, look how cute you are!

15:48.904 --> 15:50.993
Barb is gonna love
your new look.

15:51.037 --> 15:52.908
Tell her I look forward
to helping her

15:52.952 --> 15:54.518
plan the world's biggest party.

15:54.562 --> 15:55.606
-Poppy.
-[screams]

15:55.650 --> 15:57.565
-What are you doing?
-Oh. Nothing.

15:57.608 --> 15:59.001
SHEILA B:
Ooh!

15:59.045 --> 16:01.438
Poppy's busted.

16:01.482 --> 16:02.483
[shushing]

16:02.526 --> 16:04.267
BRANCH:
Sneaking out to meet Barb?

16:04.311 --> 16:05.529
Headed into enemy territory?

16:05.573 --> 16:06.530
She's not the enemy.

16:06.574 --> 16:08.315
She's a queen, the same as me.

16:08.358 --> 16:10.317
-[growling]
-[grunting]

16:11.231 --> 16:12.623
Bye-bye, little bat.

16:12.667 --> 16:15.191
Your dad just told us
that Queen Barb is bad news.

16:15.235 --> 16:16.671
Well, my dad
doesn't know everything.

16:16.714 --> 16:18.281
He knows more about this.

16:18.325 --> 16:20.544
You didn't even know there was
a string until this morning.

16:20.588 --> 16:23.199
He may be fine in a world where
everybody lives in isolation,

16:23.243 --> 16:25.114
-but I'm not.
-Well, but we don't know

16:25.158 --> 16:27.421
anything about
the other Trolls.

16:27.464 --> 16:28.988
Well, we know they're Trolls.

16:29.031 --> 16:30.772
Branch, look around
Troll Village.

16:30.815 --> 16:33.209
Everybody's different, even us.

16:33.253 --> 16:35.211
[distant sneeze]

16:35.255 --> 16:36.212
Oh.

16:36.256 --> 16:37.648
Did you hear something?

16:37.692 --> 16:39.346
Stop trying
to change the subject.

16:39.389 --> 16:41.565
Look, being queen means
having a lot of power,

16:41.609 --> 16:43.959
and it's my job
to use it for good.

16:44.003 --> 16:45.569
I can't stay home
when I know there's

16:45.613 --> 16:49.182
a world full of different
Trolls out there just like us.

16:50.052 --> 16:52.185
[sighs] This is a terrible idea

16:52.228 --> 16:54.926
that will most likely
blow up in your face.

16:54.970 --> 16:56.928
-Okay, bye.
-What?

17:03.413 --> 17:04.980
[groans]

17:09.115 --> 17:10.116
[grunts]

17:10.159 --> 17:12.814
And I guess
I'm coming with you.

17:12.857 --> 17:14.816
[sobs]:
Oh! Thank you.

17:14.859 --> 17:17.036
I really didn't want
to go by myself.

17:17.079 --> 17:19.255
-Road trip!
-Yeah!

17:24.565 --> 17:26.784
♪

17:38.274 --> 17:40.407
They areall different.

17:40.450 --> 17:44.324
[gasps softly] A-And this one
looks a little bit like me.

17:46.152 --> 17:47.370
[gasps]

17:47.414 --> 17:49.068
We even have the same hat!

17:49.111 --> 17:51.679
[echoing]: ...same hat,
same hat, same hat!

17:51.722 --> 17:53.333
♪

18:10.698 --> 18:12.613
Goodbye.

18:12.656 --> 18:15.094
I hope I see you again,
friends.

18:15.137 --> 18:18.706
But even though it's scary,
I have to go out there

18:18.749 --> 18:21.752
and see if there's
other Trolls like me.

18:23.580 --> 18:24.886
[shrieks]

18:24.929 --> 18:27.018
Oh, man, this is gonna be hard.

18:27.062 --> 18:29.499
-BARB: All aboard!
-["Crazy Train" playing]

18:29.543 --> 18:30.718
[laughing]

18:30.761 --> 18:32.981
♪ Ai, ai, ai

18:33.895 --> 18:36.115
[rock music playing loudly]

18:37.464 --> 18:39.596
♪ Crazy

18:39.640 --> 18:42.382
♪ But that's how it goes

18:44.123 --> 18:46.516
♪ Millions of people

18:46.560 --> 18:49.389
♪ Living as foes

18:51.217 --> 18:53.132
♪ Music

18:53.175 --> 18:56.178
♪ Has kept us apart

18:57.745 --> 19:00.051
♪ It's time for the hard rock

19:00.095 --> 19:03.142
♪ Revolution to start

19:04.404 --> 19:08.059
♪ No spats, no tiffs,
no fighting ♪

19:08.103 --> 19:10.801
♪ When everyone's the same

19:11.628 --> 19:13.761
♪ I'm going off the rails

19:13.804 --> 19:19.549
♪ On a crazy train!

19:19.593 --> 19:22.987
-Yeah! I got the Techno string!
-[excited chatter]

19:23.031 --> 19:25.381
Who knew world domination
could be so much fun?

19:25.425 --> 19:28.428
-Yeah! -All right, Barb!
-[Trolls cheering]

19:28.471 --> 19:29.429
All right!

19:29.472 --> 19:30.778
[both yell]

19:30.821 --> 19:33.215
Ha! Queen Barb!

19:33.259 --> 19:34.912
[both laugh]

19:34.956 --> 19:37.524
[heavy electric guitar
chord plays]

19:39.787 --> 19:42.398
[electric guitar riff plays]

19:42.442 --> 19:47.011
Only four more strings to go
until rock unites the world.

19:47.055 --> 19:48.012
[excited chatter]

19:48.056 --> 19:49.797
Dad? Where's Dad?

19:49.840 --> 19:52.234
[toilet flushes]

19:52.278 --> 19:54.454
-♪
-[engine revving]

19:58.893 --> 20:00.286
There you are, Dad.

20:00.329 --> 20:02.462
-I got the Techno string.
-Cool.

20:02.505 --> 20:04.333
-What's a string ag-again?
-[back-up alarm beeping]

20:04.377 --> 20:05.465
What? Uh...

20:05.508 --> 20:07.118
-Don't you remember the plan?
-Plan?

20:07.162 --> 20:09.120
-I don't remember... [mumbles]
-Oh.

20:09.164 --> 20:10.339
-Great idea, man.
-Whoa.

20:10.383 --> 20:11.427
Okay, guys, line up.

20:11.471 --> 20:12.907
We're gonna go over
the plan again.

20:12.950 --> 20:13.951
[Trolls murmur, chuckle]

20:13.995 --> 20:16.563
Okay. We're on a World Tour.

20:16.606 --> 20:19.609
And on each stop,
we get a new string.

20:19.653 --> 20:21.132
When I have all six strings,

20:21.176 --> 20:23.744
I'll play the ultimate
power chord.

20:23.787 --> 20:25.136
[electric guitar chord plays]

20:25.180 --> 20:28.966
And I will unite the Trolls
under one music.

20:29.010 --> 20:30.272
Our music!

20:30.316 --> 20:31.969
-TROLLS: Rock!
-[excited chatter]

20:34.842 --> 20:36.409
Oh, here it comes.

20:39.934 --> 20:42.632
[grunting slowly]

20:42.676 --> 20:44.678
Uh, just a little bit more.

20:44.721 --> 20:46.114
Riff, just help him, man.

20:46.157 --> 20:47.333
Yes, Your Rockness.

20:47.376 --> 20:48.725
Aw.

20:48.769 --> 20:49.813
There it is.

20:49.857 --> 20:51.815
-[Trolls cheering]
-BARB: Yeah!

20:51.859 --> 20:53.513
-Rock and roll!
-Yeah!

20:53.556 --> 20:54.644
[both laugh]

20:54.688 --> 20:55.863
Yeah!

20:59.867 --> 21:01.651
[inhales deeply]

21:01.695 --> 21:03.523
-[sighs]
-All right.

21:03.566 --> 21:07.266
In a short 456 pages, I'm gonna
know how to fly this thing.

21:07.309 --> 21:08.963
-[knuckles crack]
-Ugh, Branch,

21:09.006 --> 21:11.052
we don't need
a giant, comprehensive manual.

21:11.095 --> 21:12.358
-[grunts]
-[gasps]

21:12.401 --> 21:13.620
How hard can it be?
♪ Doo-doo-doo-doo-doo.

21:13.663 --> 21:16.187
-[console beeping]
-♪ Try one of these.

21:16.231 --> 21:19.974
[Sheila B whooping, laughing]

21:20.017 --> 21:21.802
All right, Poppy!

21:21.845 --> 21:23.325
Easy on the buttons!

21:23.369 --> 21:24.370
-Sorry.
-[snoring nearby]

21:24.413 --> 21:26.502
[shushes]
What was that?

21:26.546 --> 21:27.503
[sleepy murmur]

21:27.547 --> 21:29.505
[whistling exhale]

21:29.549 --> 21:30.680
[sleepy murmur]

21:30.724 --> 21:31.855
[snoring]

21:31.899 --> 21:33.509
[Mr. Dinkles sucking, cooing]

21:33.553 --> 21:34.858
Biggie?

21:34.902 --> 21:36.120
Oh, hello.

21:36.164 --> 21:37.861
Sorry. I couldn't help myself.

21:37.905 --> 21:39.689
You know how I am
around cotton candy.

21:39.733 --> 21:40.864
-[burps]
-Oh, dear.

21:40.908 --> 21:41.865
Now look what's happened.

21:41.909 --> 21:44.346
Mr. Dinkles got all gummed up.

21:44.390 --> 21:45.913
-[squeaks]
-[gasps] Mr. Dinkles!

21:45.956 --> 21:47.088
Mr. Dinkles!

21:47.131 --> 21:48.350
Oh, there you are.
I thought you were--

21:48.394 --> 21:50.831
Oh. Right, then.
We'll just be on our way--

21:50.874 --> 21:52.223
[screams] Hey!

21:52.267 --> 21:54.748
Poppy, wh-where are you
balloon-flying us to?

21:54.791 --> 21:57.272
We're on a mission
to help Barb unite the Trolls,

21:57.316 --> 21:59.535
and I'm so glad
you're coming with us.

21:59.579 --> 22:00.884
I did what in the who now?

22:00.928 --> 22:02.321
Hey, man, join the club.

22:02.364 --> 22:04.366
And I hope you didn't eat
all the cotton candy,

22:04.410 --> 22:06.325
because Barb is gonna love it.

22:06.368 --> 22:07.935
[clears throat]
Branchifer?

22:07.978 --> 22:09.197
[clears throat]
Y-Yes, Poppifer?

22:09.240 --> 22:11.199
-What is this?
-Oh, it's nothing, nothing.

22:11.242 --> 22:13.157
-That-that-that-that's
just my man stuff. -[gasps]

22:13.201 --> 22:14.507
I love man stuff!

22:14.550 --> 22:16.378
Weapons?

22:16.422 --> 22:18.119
Ugh. For shame.

22:18.162 --> 22:19.338
Well, I-I...

22:19.381 --> 22:21.122
Violence never solves
a problem, Branch.

22:21.165 --> 22:22.906
-[squeaks]
-[shrieks]

22:22.950 --> 22:24.908
I'm not saying
we have to use them.

22:24.952 --> 22:26.736
I'm just saying
it's better to be prepared

22:26.780 --> 22:28.390
in case we need them.

22:28.434 --> 22:31.262
We won't need them unless these
pointy sticks help you listen

22:31.306 --> 22:32.960
or these rocks help you
put yourself

22:33.003 --> 22:34.222
in someone else's shoes.

22:34.265 --> 22:35.745
And what about these?
Is this-- What, I--

22:35.789 --> 22:36.964
Is this some kind of jewelry?

22:37.007 --> 22:37.921
Oh, it's actually
kind of cool-looking.

22:37.965 --> 22:38.922
♪ Oh.

22:38.966 --> 22:40.315
Gi-Give me that.

22:40.359 --> 22:43.187
We don't even know
what's out there.

22:46.582 --> 22:49.063
Wait! No-- Oh, man.

22:49.106 --> 22:51.631
By the way,
I whittled those for hours.

22:51.674 --> 22:56.375
Branch, the only weapons we
need are this guy and this guy,

22:56.418 --> 22:57.463
for hugs!

22:57.506 --> 23:00.117
Uh, you may want
to take a look at this.

23:00.161 --> 23:02.337
♪

23:05.035 --> 23:07.081
[fire crackling softly]

23:08.082 --> 23:11.128
This is gonna take
a lot of hugs.

23:11.172 --> 23:13.392
♪

23:25.012 --> 23:26.143
Whoa.

23:26.187 --> 23:28.450
Something gnarly happened here.

23:28.494 --> 23:30.147
PENNYWHISTLE:
Hello?

23:30.191 --> 23:31.801
Who said that?

23:31.845 --> 23:34.325
Identify yourself!

23:34.369 --> 23:39.113
PENNYWHISTLE: Uh, are you nice
or are you mean?

23:39.156 --> 23:41.245
W-We're nice.
We're really nice.

23:41.289 --> 23:43.247
Yeah, but not too nice.

23:43.291 --> 23:46.207
So don't even try it.

23:48.035 --> 23:49.515
Okay.

23:54.084 --> 23:55.608
[softly]:
Oh. Hi.

23:55.651 --> 23:57.479
What is this place?

23:57.523 --> 24:00.830
It used to be called
Symphonyville.

24:00.874 --> 24:02.223
[coughs]

24:02.266 --> 24:05.008
Where the Classical Music
Trolls lived.

24:05.052 --> 24:09.230
But that was in the before.

24:09.273 --> 24:10.753
What happened here?

24:10.797 --> 24:16.280
Well, it was the most wonderful
place you ever did seen.

24:16.324 --> 24:18.892
[lively classical music
playing, chatter, laughter]

24:18.935 --> 24:20.720
It was a place where all of

24:20.763 --> 24:25.159
the Classical Music Trolls
could live in perfect harmony.

24:25.202 --> 24:27.422
[classical music continues]

24:28.249 --> 24:29.859
[laughs]:
Ooh.

24:29.903 --> 24:33.559
Wherever the conductor led,
we followed.

24:33.602 --> 24:36.431
Play, play. [vocalizes]
Beautiful.

24:36.475 --> 24:39.956
-[laughs] -But then Queen Barb showed up.

24:40.000 --> 24:41.044
Oh, no.

24:41.088 --> 24:42.698
'Sup, Trollzart dude?

24:42.742 --> 24:44.831
I'm here for your string.

24:44.874 --> 24:46.876
We will not go quietly.

24:46.920 --> 24:48.704
[playing Beethoven's
"Symphony No. 5 in C Minor"]

24:48.748 --> 24:50.184
-[triangle dings]
-[Barb snores]

24:50.227 --> 24:51.838
[sighs]:
Mi, mi, mi, mi, mi.

24:51.881 --> 24:54.536
Oh. Oh, I'm sorry,
I-I must have fallen asleep,

24:54.580 --> 24:57.539
because your music
is so boring.

24:57.583 --> 24:58.584
[scoffs]

24:58.627 --> 25:00.063
Where are the words, bro?
Right?

25:00.107 --> 25:01.325
Now give me your string.

25:01.369 --> 25:03.632
[amplifier buzzes, hums]

25:03.676 --> 25:06.069
[playing Beethoven's
"Symphony No. 5 in C Minor"]

25:06.113 --> 25:08.202
-Oh! Oh!
-[Trolls gasping]

25:09.029 --> 25:11.161
[sighs] No.

25:12.293 --> 25:14.251
PENNYWHISTLE:
She took our string.

25:14.295 --> 25:15.426
Our-our music.

25:15.470 --> 25:18.952
She took everyone.

25:18.995 --> 25:20.867
[wind whistling softly]

25:20.910 --> 25:24.305
We lost everything.

25:27.003 --> 25:29.353
Barb doesn't want to unite us.

25:30.441 --> 25:32.618
She wants to destroy us.

25:40.321 --> 25:43.454
We need to make sure
our own string is safe.

25:43.498 --> 25:46.457
Uh, our string is safe.

25:46.501 --> 25:47.458
What?!

25:47.502 --> 25:48.938
Poppy, are-are you crazy?

25:48.982 --> 25:50.940
I thought it was a good idea
at the time.

25:50.984 --> 25:54.465
I-I can't believe another queen
would use her power for evil.

25:54.509 --> 25:55.771
Okay. Change of plans.

25:55.815 --> 25:57.468
We need to get home
as fast as we can

25:57.512 --> 25:58.731
and get everyone in the bunker.

25:58.774 --> 26:00.559
Uh, no. Change of plans.

26:00.602 --> 26:02.952
We have to stop Barb
from destroying all music.

26:02.996 --> 26:04.737
If we don't stop her, who will?

26:04.780 --> 26:06.608
Poppy, you said this could be
handled with hugs.

26:06.652 --> 26:09.045
How are we gonna hug
our way out of this one?

26:09.089 --> 26:10.264
-It's okay, Biggie.
-Really?

26:10.307 --> 26:11.874
It's okay to be terrified?

26:11.918 --> 26:13.963
When am I gonna learn to stay
away from the cotton candy?!

26:14.007 --> 26:14.964
No.

26:15.008 --> 26:16.400
As your queen,

26:16.444 --> 26:19.229
I promise that I will
protect you, no matter what.

26:19.273 --> 26:22.929
I... pinky promise.

26:22.972 --> 26:24.844
[gasps]

26:24.887 --> 26:29.457
Poppy, you know you can't
go back on a pinky promise.

26:29.500 --> 26:31.981
Never did, never will.

26:32.025 --> 26:35.289
♪

26:35.332 --> 26:37.073
-[electricity crackles]
-[magic jingling]

26:37.117 --> 26:39.336
[wind whooshing]

26:42.122 --> 26:43.993
[laughs]

26:44.037 --> 26:45.429
Farewell!

26:48.650 --> 26:50.826
A pinky promise.

26:50.870 --> 26:52.306
Dang.

26:55.352 --> 26:57.137
Let it be so.

26:57.180 --> 26:59.705
And so it is.

26:59.748 --> 27:00.836
[groans]

27:00.880 --> 27:03.447
This just got real.

27:03.491 --> 27:05.232
POPPY: We have to get to
the Country Music Trolls

27:05.275 --> 27:07.800
in Lonesome Flats
before Barb does.

27:07.843 --> 27:09.540
Will you come with us?

27:09.584 --> 27:10.498
Oh, no.

27:10.541 --> 27:12.892
Someone has to rebuild.

27:12.935 --> 27:18.332
And Pennywhistle is
that woodwind for the job.

27:19.159 --> 27:20.769
[grunts]

27:27.254 --> 27:28.995
Good luck, little Pennywhistle.

27:30.039 --> 27:32.259
Goodbye, Poppy.

27:35.610 --> 27:36.785
[sighs]

27:37.656 --> 27:39.919
[whooping, excited shouting]

27:39.962 --> 27:42.661
[growling]

27:43.749 --> 27:45.881
Wait. Is that...

27:45.925 --> 27:47.100
-Debbie?
-Oh, what?

27:47.143 --> 27:48.579
-Oh, that's a lot of glitter.
-BARB: No!

27:48.623 --> 27:50.669
What did they do to you,
my hairy little baby?!

27:50.712 --> 27:51.887
Come here, come here,
come here.

27:51.931 --> 27:53.410
-Gnarly.
-What-what-what do you...

27:53.454 --> 27:55.238
-What is this?
-What, what...

27:55.282 --> 27:56.892
Pop Trolls?

27:56.936 --> 27:57.980
[clears throat]

27:58.024 --> 28:00.722
"Dear Barb,
can't wait to meet you.

28:00.766 --> 28:03.333
I have tons of
great party ideas."

28:03.377 --> 28:04.726
I like that.

28:04.770 --> 28:07.511
"Maybe you and I
can even be best friends."

28:07.555 --> 28:08.904
Best friends?

28:08.948 --> 28:10.950
Is she making fun of me?

28:10.993 --> 28:12.908
No one says that.

28:12.952 --> 28:15.911
Friendship takes time and years
of mutual care and respect.

28:15.955 --> 28:17.783
You don't just become
best friends.

28:17.826 --> 28:21.743
Plus, everyone knows I already
have a ton of friends.

28:21.787 --> 28:22.875
Like Carol.

28:22.918 --> 28:24.485
Right, Carol?

28:25.573 --> 28:27.488
Okay, you're busy.
That's fine.

28:27.531 --> 28:28.489
Love you, Carol.

28:28.532 --> 28:30.796
[quiet crackling]

28:33.886 --> 28:36.627
POPPY [over speaker]:
♪ Trolls just wanna have fun.

28:36.671 --> 28:37.585
[growls]

28:37.628 --> 28:39.282
-Gnarly.
-[back-up alarm beeping]

28:39.326 --> 28:41.763
Pop music isn't even
real music!

28:41.807 --> 28:44.940
It's bland! It's repetitive!

28:44.984 --> 28:47.116
The lyrics are empty!

28:47.160 --> 28:51.120
Worst of all, it crawls into
your head like an earworm!

28:51.164 --> 28:53.775
[chain saw buzzing]

28:53.819 --> 28:55.255
[sighs]

28:55.298 --> 28:57.474
You know, and you can't
get it out-- Uh, I'm tired now.

28:57.518 --> 29:00.216
[whoops] Hating things
takes a lot of energy.

29:00.260 --> 29:02.784
♪ Trolls just wanna have fun

29:02.828 --> 29:04.438
-♪ Trolls just wanna...
-No. No.

29:04.481 --> 29:05.874
Look what their music
just did to Dad.

29:05.918 --> 29:07.310
-Daddy? Come back.
-[slurping]

29:07.354 --> 29:08.747
Come back to me, Daddy.

29:09.922 --> 29:11.662
Nice hair, dude.

29:11.706 --> 29:13.664
No one does this to Dad.

29:13.708 --> 29:15.971
And no one makes fun
of Queen Barb.

29:16.015 --> 29:16.842
[humming]

29:16.885 --> 29:19.540
Ah! I need that Pop string.

29:19.583 --> 29:21.847
And I know who's gonna help me.

29:21.890 --> 29:25.415
The most feared bounty hunters
in all of Trolldom.

29:25.459 --> 29:27.504
-[smooth jazz music playing]
-[bell dings]

29:27.548 --> 29:30.812
Chaz, the Smooth Jazz Troll.

29:30.856 --> 29:32.988
-["Mi Gente" playing]
-The Reggaeton Trolls.

29:33.032 --> 29:35.077
-["Russian Roulette" playing]
-♪ La, la-la-la...

29:35.121 --> 29:37.210
BARB:
The K-Pop Gang.

29:37.253 --> 29:39.647
-["Hocus Pocus" playing,
singer yodeling] -And...

29:39.690 --> 29:41.214
the Yodelers.

29:41.257 --> 29:42.215
Okay.

29:42.258 --> 29:43.825
As you probably know,

29:43.869 --> 29:46.915
I'm bringing a tidal wave of
rock across this land of ours.

29:46.959 --> 29:48.874
♪

29:48.917 --> 29:51.180
And soon there will be
nothing but hard rock

29:51.224 --> 29:53.008
as far as the ear can hear.

29:53.052 --> 29:56.098
Whoever brings me Queen Poppy
gets to keep

29:56.142 --> 30:00.102
their very own music
in their very own territory.

30:00.146 --> 30:02.626
Right over here.

30:02.670 --> 30:03.932
-[Trolls murmuring, groaning]
-TROLL: Oh.

30:03.976 --> 30:05.673
I don't know.
It looks pretty tiny.

30:05.716 --> 30:07.066
You want it or not?

30:08.545 --> 30:11.592
All you have to do is
get me Queen Poppy!

30:11.635 --> 30:13.420
-Oh, okay. -Sounds like
a pretty good deal.

30:13.463 --> 30:14.856
Do you validate parking?

30:14.900 --> 30:16.727
Dude, where are the Yodelers?

30:16.771 --> 30:18.729
I heard a rumor, uh,
that they yodeled so hard,

30:18.773 --> 30:20.427
an avalanche fell on 'em.

30:21.515 --> 30:23.169
Or something.

30:23.212 --> 30:25.519
Well, I don't pay you to hear.

30:25.562 --> 30:28.043
Actually, I'm doing this
for college credit.

30:28.087 --> 30:32.091
If anyone can find me
Queen Poppy and her string,

30:32.134 --> 30:34.267
-it's the Yodelers.
-♪ Just wanna have fun...

30:34.310 --> 30:35.834
[music distorts, stops]

30:39.141 --> 30:41.622
This must be where
the Country Music Trolls live.

30:41.665 --> 30:42.928
Well, it looks like
nobody's here.

30:42.971 --> 30:44.581
We're too late.
Time to go home.

30:44.625 --> 30:45.756
Come on, guys, let's go.

30:45.800 --> 30:48.890
There is no "I quit" in "team."

30:52.154 --> 30:54.896
Cock-a-doodle--

30:54.940 --> 30:57.203
Ah, never mind.

30:57.246 --> 30:59.640
[solemn country music playing]

31:00.467 --> 31:01.903
[bell chimes]

31:04.950 --> 31:07.778
♪ We don't hope for

31:07.822 --> 31:10.694
♪ Making things better

31:11.521 --> 31:14.698
♪ All we want is to

31:14.742 --> 31:17.919
♪ Keep it together

31:17.963 --> 31:20.052
-[giggles]
-♪ Every day is a rainy day

31:20.095 --> 31:22.054
-Happy birthday, honey.
-♪ No change in the weather

31:22.097 --> 31:23.969
-Time to get to work.
-[yak breathing noisily]

31:24.012 --> 31:25.187
Okay, Daddy.

31:25.231 --> 31:26.536
-♪ This kind of life
-[milk spraying]

31:26.580 --> 31:28.799
-♪ Has made our hearts
-[children laughing]

31:28.843 --> 31:30.671
-♪ As hard as leather
-Get it.

31:30.714 --> 31:32.716
[playful chatter]

31:32.760 --> 31:33.979
-[tumbleweed yelling]
-[children screaming]

31:34.022 --> 31:36.285
♪ And all these tears
are from ♪

31:36.329 --> 31:40.159
♪ The dust in our eyes

31:40.202 --> 31:41.943
-[Troll crying]
-♪ And all these years

31:41.987 --> 31:43.684
-[tear crying]
-♪ Just keep on

31:43.727 --> 31:47.035
♪ Passing us by

31:47.079 --> 31:50.169
♪ We all know that we're just

31:50.212 --> 31:54.086
-♪ Born to die
-[yaks mooing]

31:54.129 --> 31:57.263
♪ That's the way it goes
when you're just ♪

31:57.306 --> 32:00.179
♪ Born to die

32:00.222 --> 32:03.138
This song is so sad.

32:03.182 --> 32:05.314
Yeah, it is sad.

32:05.358 --> 32:10.189
But life is sad sometimes,
so I kind of like it.

32:10.232 --> 32:12.626
You do? Huh.

32:12.669 --> 32:14.671
But it's so different.

32:14.715 --> 32:16.064
Oh, they must not know

32:16.108 --> 32:18.414
that music's
supposed to make you happy.

32:18.458 --> 32:20.721
[gasps] That's awful.

32:21.896 --> 32:24.943
♪ And all these years
just keep on ♪

32:24.986 --> 32:28.163
♪ Passing us by

32:28.207 --> 32:30.861
-[Trolls grunting, arguing]
-♪ And all this misery

32:30.905 --> 32:34.691
♪ Makes it hard to deny

32:34.735 --> 32:36.911
-[grunting]
-♪ That's the way it goes

32:36.955 --> 32:38.521
♪ When you're just

32:38.565 --> 32:42.743
♪ Born to die.

32:46.877 --> 32:49.271
Okay, guys, guys, huddle up.

32:49.315 --> 32:50.359
[bird screeches in distance]

32:50.403 --> 32:51.926
[growling]:
Growly, growly, growl.

32:51.970 --> 32:53.667
Now, take it easy, Growly Pete.

32:53.710 --> 32:55.016
I feel bad for them.

32:55.060 --> 32:57.714
It looks like they got
beat up by a rainbow.

32:57.758 --> 32:59.020
First things first,

32:59.064 --> 33:00.804
these Trolls need
some serious cheering up,

33:00.848 --> 33:02.893
and we're gonna
have to go top-shelf.

33:02.937 --> 33:03.807
Oh.

33:03.851 --> 33:05.853
Now, when you say "top-shelf,"

33:05.896 --> 33:07.202
-y-you don't mean...
-That's right.

33:07.246 --> 33:09.552
We need to sing them
the most important songs

33:09.596 --> 33:12.468
in the history of music.

33:12.512 --> 33:14.122
Yes, but which ones?

33:15.167 --> 33:16.342
All of them.

33:16.385 --> 33:18.692
And when you say
"all of them..."

33:18.735 --> 33:19.954
-♪ Yo, I'll tell you what
I want ♪ -["Wannabe" playing]

33:19.998 --> 33:21.608
♪ What I really, really want

33:21.651 --> 33:23.175
♪ So tell me what you want,
what you really, really want ♪

33:23.218 --> 33:24.828
♪ I'll tell you what I want,
what I really, really want ♪

33:24.872 --> 33:26.569
♪ So tell me what you want,
what you really, really want ♪

33:26.613 --> 33:28.397
-♪ I wanna, I wanna, I wanna,
I wanna ♪ - Ha, ha, ha, ha ♪

33:28.441 --> 33:30.399
♪ I wanna really, really,
really wanna zig-a-zag, ah ♪

33:30.443 --> 33:32.010
-♪ Who? Who? Who-who?
-["Who Let the Dogs Out" plays]

33:32.053 --> 33:34.099
♪ Who let the dogs out?

33:34.142 --> 33:36.405
-♪ Who? Who? Who-who?
-[squeaking rhythmically]

33:36.449 --> 33:38.320
♪ Who let the dogs out?

33:38.364 --> 33:39.974
♪ Who? Who? Who-who?

33:40.018 --> 33:41.367
-♪ It's such a good vibration
-["Good Vibrations" playing]

33:41.410 --> 33:43.586
♪ Yeah, come on,
come on, come on ♪

33:43.630 --> 33:45.588
♪ It's such a sweet sensation

33:45.632 --> 33:47.808
-♪ Oppa Gangnam style
-["Gangnam Style" playing]

33:47.851 --> 33:49.853
[rhythmic grunting]

33:49.897 --> 33:51.246
♪ Gangnam style

33:51.290 --> 33:53.074
♪ O-O-O-O

33:53.118 --> 33:54.597
-♪ Oppa Gangnam style
-["Hey Baby" playing]

33:54.641 --> 33:56.904
♪ Hey, pretty girl,
what you doing tonight? ♪

33:56.947 --> 33:58.384
-♪ Gangnam style
-♪ I wanna see

33:58.427 --> 34:00.168
-♪ What you got in store
-♪ O-O-O-O

34:00.212 --> 34:02.388
-♪ Oppa Gangnam style
-["Party Rock Anthem" playing]

34:02.431 --> 34:05.478
♪ Party rock is
in the house tonight ♪

34:05.521 --> 34:08.785
-Come on! -♪ Everybody just
have a good time ♪

34:08.829 --> 34:12.615
-Rave on, party on! -♪ Party
rock is in the house tonight ♪

34:12.659 --> 34:14.835
♪ We just wanna see ya

34:14.878 --> 34:16.097
♪ Tell 'em, Poppy

34:16.141 --> 34:17.620
[echoing]:
♪ Shake that.

34:17.664 --> 34:19.840
[wind whistling softly]

34:21.407 --> 34:23.104
TUMBLEWEED:
You suck!

34:26.151 --> 34:28.762
Now, I want you three
to sit in here

34:28.805 --> 34:30.894
and think about
what you've just done.

34:30.938 --> 34:33.549
-That was a crime against
music. -POPPY: Wait, no.

34:33.593 --> 34:37.118
We're here to warn you
about Barb, the Queen of Rock.

34:37.162 --> 34:39.294
[sighs] Sweetie, I already know

34:39.338 --> 34:43.820
and have heard about this Queen
Barb and her fancy World Tour.

34:43.864 --> 34:45.300
Now, if you'll excuse me,

34:45.344 --> 34:50.436
I got to go wash what you call
music out of my ears.

34:50.479 --> 34:51.654
[gasps]

34:51.698 --> 34:52.655
[chuckles]:
Oh.

34:52.699 --> 34:54.353
You in real trouble now.

34:54.396 --> 34:55.658
Right, Aunt Delta?

34:55.702 --> 34:58.052
-Keep an eye on 'em,
Growly Pete. -Yes!

34:58.096 --> 35:00.141
Growly, growly, growly, growl.

35:00.185 --> 35:03.797
No, no. Music should bring us
together, not divide us!

35:03.840 --> 35:06.539
-Sugar.
-[sighs]

35:06.582 --> 35:08.584
Well, I knew it.

35:08.628 --> 35:11.370
"Who Let the Dogs Out."
Too far.

35:11.413 --> 35:12.893
Okay, Branch.

35:12.936 --> 35:16.026
You can say "I told you so."
I know you want to.

35:17.854 --> 35:20.814
♪

35:25.862 --> 35:28.126
Y-You did great
out there, Poppy.

35:29.562 --> 35:30.606
[Poppy shrieks]

35:30.650 --> 35:31.868
I'll never survive
the big house.

35:31.912 --> 35:34.044
-We've got to get out of here.
-I know.

35:34.088 --> 35:36.699
That was such a rad medley.
I can't believe it didn't work.

35:36.743 --> 35:38.397
Tell me about it.
I did the splits.

35:38.440 --> 35:39.789
No one even clapped.

35:39.833 --> 35:41.313
Am I not cute anymore?!

35:41.356 --> 35:42.314
Come on!

35:42.357 --> 35:44.185
Maybe my dad was right.

35:44.229 --> 35:47.101
The other Trolls are different
in ways I was not prepared for.

35:47.145 --> 35:50.409
Some Trolls, they don't
just want to have fun.

35:50.452 --> 35:53.542
Anybody got a plan B?

35:53.586 --> 35:55.936
Plan B? Right up here.

35:58.068 --> 36:01.202
Step one:
escape from Lonesome Flats.

36:02.551 --> 36:05.902
[snorting, spitting noisily]

36:05.946 --> 36:07.513
[sighs] Plan B it is.

36:07.556 --> 36:09.384
I guess we're going home.

36:09.428 --> 36:10.864
HICKORY:
Whoo-hey!

36:10.907 --> 36:12.126
[screams]

36:13.127 --> 36:15.477
It ain't right
to put you in jail

36:15.521 --> 36:17.740
'cause your music's different.

36:17.784 --> 36:19.177
It seems some folks round here

36:19.220 --> 36:20.917
don't appreciate a rad medley
when they hear one.

36:20.961 --> 36:22.136
[bell dings]

36:22.832 --> 36:24.094
Let's skedaddle.

36:24.138 --> 36:26.227
Yes! Mission back on!

36:26.271 --> 36:28.969
Branch! Branch!
You can stop rescuing us.

36:29.796 --> 36:31.754
[gasps]

36:31.798 --> 36:33.669
Poppy, you don't even know
who this is.

36:33.713 --> 36:35.454
I'm Queen Poppy.
What's your name?

36:35.497 --> 36:36.759
Name's Hickory.

36:36.803 --> 36:38.370
Branch, this is Hickory.
Hickory, this is Branch.

36:38.413 --> 36:40.198
Enough with the formalities.
Let's go!

36:40.241 --> 36:42.983
-Uh, this is Mr. Dinkles,
by the way. -[squeaks]

36:44.158 --> 36:45.986
I said let's skedaddle! Hyah!

36:46.029 --> 36:47.596
Go get 'em, Clampers!

36:47.640 --> 36:49.337
[hisses, blabbering]

36:49.381 --> 36:50.817
♪

36:50.860 --> 36:53.123
[screams] This was
my plan C, by the way.

36:53.167 --> 36:54.864
♪ I feel it coming like
a highball train ♪

36:54.908 --> 36:56.562
-Charge!
-♪ Bearing down on

36:56.605 --> 36:58.781
-♪ The end of the line
-[Hickory shouting]

36:58.825 --> 37:00.261
Hyah! Hyah!

37:00.305 --> 37:01.523
♪ I see the black clouds...

37:01.567 --> 37:02.698
POPPY:
Oh, no! Hickory!

37:02.742 --> 37:04.352
I got it, Queen Poppy.

37:04.396 --> 37:06.441
DELTA DAWN:
Don't let them get away!

37:06.485 --> 37:07.747
[screaming, shouting]

37:07.790 --> 37:09.705
♪ I'm feeling meaner
than an old bobcat ♪

37:09.749 --> 37:11.011
[Biggie sobbing]

37:11.054 --> 37:12.273
-[blabbering]
-♪ I got the hammer down

37:12.317 --> 37:14.536
-♪ And won't look back
-[laughs]

37:14.580 --> 37:17.278
♪ My mind is headed down
a one-way track ♪

37:17.322 --> 37:21.021
♪ I'm leaving Lonesome Flats,
I'm leaving Lonesome Flats ♪

37:21.064 --> 37:23.023
[whoops] Yeah!

37:23.066 --> 37:24.285
[blabbering]

37:24.329 --> 37:25.330
[screams]

37:26.374 --> 37:27.984
Yeah! [whoops]

37:28.028 --> 37:29.812
-Come on, Growly Pete!
-Uh-oh.

37:29.856 --> 37:30.987
-Do your thing!
-[whooping]

37:31.031 --> 37:32.467
No one can escape my mustache.

37:32.511 --> 37:33.816
That's how you do it!

37:33.860 --> 37:35.383
[gasping]

37:35.427 --> 37:37.255
-Hyah!
-[laughs] That tickles.

37:37.298 --> 37:39.474
Branch, hold on to Mr. Dinkles!

37:39.518 --> 37:40.780
[yelling]

37:40.823 --> 37:42.869
[straining]

37:42.912 --> 37:45.132
[yelling and straining
continue]

37:47.482 --> 37:50.137
-Hyah!
-We're gonna get you now!

37:55.360 --> 37:57.318
[screaming]

37:57.362 --> 37:58.363
[whoops]

37:58.406 --> 38:00.669
POPPY:
Hickory, look out!

38:00.713 --> 38:02.541
[blabbering]

38:04.369 --> 38:05.674
We're not gonna make it!

38:05.718 --> 38:08.068
Oh, yes, we are.

38:10.940 --> 38:14.944
-♪ Yeah, I'm leaving
Lonesome Flats. ♪ -[screaming]

38:14.988 --> 38:17.686
Well, I hope
Pop Trolls can swim.

38:17.730 --> 38:19.949
[screaming]

38:22.474 --> 38:23.997
Oh, for Pete's sake.

38:24.040 --> 38:26.913
-Well, dangity-doodly.
-Dangity-doodly.

38:26.956 --> 38:28.523
[Clampers grunts]

38:28.567 --> 38:31.570
[relaxing music playing]

38:44.757 --> 38:45.975
[squeaks]

38:46.019 --> 38:49.065
Welcome home.

38:49.109 --> 38:51.416
[choir singing]

38:51.459 --> 38:54.984
[music distorting]

38:58.597 --> 39:00.512
-[coughs, pops]
-[gasps]

39:00.555 --> 39:01.426
[squeaking]

39:01.469 --> 39:03.166
Oh, Mr. Dinkles, you're alive.

39:03.210 --> 39:05.386
For a minute there, I thought
you'd kicked the bucket.

39:05.430 --> 39:07.301
[groans]

39:07.345 --> 39:10.826
[Poppy and Branch
coughing, panting]

39:10.870 --> 39:12.828
I'm really glad
you came with me.

39:12.872 --> 39:14.700
[panting]

39:14.743 --> 39:15.788
-Me, too.
-[galloping]

39:15.831 --> 39:17.093
HICKORY:
Yah!

39:17.137 --> 39:18.399
There you are. Whew!

39:18.443 --> 39:19.922
-I think we lost them.
-[grunting]

39:19.966 --> 39:21.576
-We should be all right.
-Thank you.

39:21.620 --> 39:23.752
I don't know
how we can ever repay you.

39:23.796 --> 39:25.580
Oh, wait! Yes, I do.

39:25.624 --> 39:26.625
Gumdrops!

39:26.668 --> 39:27.974
Gum what?

39:28.017 --> 39:30.411
Oh. Well, thank you.

39:30.455 --> 39:32.326
Whew. That's got a zing,
don't it?

39:32.370 --> 39:34.284
-Uh... Whoa.
-It's not candy time.

39:34.328 --> 39:35.721
It's question time.

39:35.764 --> 39:36.722
-[bell dings]
-Huh?

39:36.765 --> 39:38.071
-Hug time!
-Hug time!

39:38.114 --> 39:39.942
-Ooh. Oh, that feels good.
-Wow.

39:39.986 --> 39:41.596
[grunts]

39:41.640 --> 39:44.294
-Why are you helping us?
-[bell dings]

39:44.338 --> 39:45.948
What's in it for you?

39:45.992 --> 39:47.210
Hey! Branch.

39:47.254 --> 39:50.953
[chuckles] I'm sorry
about my... associate.

39:50.997 --> 39:52.433
HICKORY:
I loved your message about

39:52.477 --> 39:54.043
music bringing Trolls together.

39:54.087 --> 39:58.700
You may be Pop, and I may be
Country, but Trolls is Trolls.

39:58.744 --> 40:00.441
[imitates Hickory]:
"Trolls is Trolls."

40:00.485 --> 40:01.877
Wow. Deep.

40:01.921 --> 40:04.619
This is the beginning of
a partnership between Trolls

40:04.663 --> 40:07.100
that's going to save
all Trolls.

