It's why all our strings
are different.

53:03.092 --> 53:05.443
Because they reflect
our different music.

53:05.486 --> 53:08.185
Denying our differences

53:08.228 --> 53:11.275
is denying the truth
of who we are.

53:13.146 --> 53:15.453
I hadn't thought of it
like that.

53:15.496 --> 53:18.238
-[alarm wailing]
-[gasps]

53:18.282 --> 53:20.501
Rock has arrived!
It's on!

53:21.372 --> 53:22.590
Prepare for battle!

53:22.634 --> 53:24.853
["Move On Up"
by Curtis Mayfield playing]

53:25.680 --> 53:27.204
[records scratching]

53:31.686 --> 53:33.384
[over speaker]:
Assemble the crew.

53:35.429 --> 53:37.344
♪ Bite your lip

53:38.215 --> 53:41.000
♪ And take a trip

53:42.306 --> 53:44.264
♪ Though there may be
wet road ahead ♪

53:44.308 --> 53:46.092
I'm gonna make sure
you get to safety.

53:46.135 --> 53:48.094
♪ And you cannot slip

53:48.921 --> 53:50.270
-No. No!
-♪ Move on up

53:50.314 --> 53:51.750
Let me help you!

53:51.793 --> 53:53.708
-♪ And keep on...
-[music slows, stops]

53:53.752 --> 53:54.796
Aw, you kidding me?

53:54.840 --> 53:57.103
[giggles]

53:57.146 --> 54:00.062
-Hard Rock cut the power.
-They're fighting dirty.

54:00.106 --> 54:01.890
-POPPY: Cooper!
-[Trolls clamoring]

54:07.156 --> 54:08.549
-Hickory.
-HICKORY: Don't worry!

54:08.593 --> 54:10.551
I'll find you guys.

54:10.595 --> 54:13.206
Uh, Poppy.

54:13.250 --> 54:14.816
-[engines revving]
-[rock music playing]

54:14.860 --> 54:16.514
BARB:
Rock on!

54:16.557 --> 54:18.298
[Branch whimpering]

54:18.342 --> 54:20.257
[Poppy grunts]

54:24.348 --> 54:25.740
No! [grunts]

54:25.784 --> 54:27.829
We have to get back down there.
There's still hope.

54:27.873 --> 54:30.179
-We can still fix this.
-Poppy, enough.

54:30.223 --> 54:32.051
I've listened to you
and I've done it your way,

54:32.094 --> 54:34.096
and now it's your turn
to listen.

54:34.140 --> 54:36.185
It's time to get back home.

54:36.229 --> 54:38.492
I'm not like you.
I can't just give up.

54:38.536 --> 54:39.711
Give up?

54:39.754 --> 54:41.495
I want to protect
our friends and family.

54:41.539 --> 54:45.412
I can't go home until I've
proven myself as a good queen.

54:45.456 --> 54:47.675
So that's what this is
really all about?

54:47.719 --> 54:49.155
Why are you so upset?

54:49.198 --> 54:50.809
Because your dad was right

54:50.852 --> 54:53.333
and Biggie was right
and Queen Essence was right.

54:53.377 --> 54:57.337
And I've been backing you up
even when you ignore them.

54:59.905 --> 55:02.081
But you never listen to me.

55:02.124 --> 55:04.170
Branch, what are you
talking about?

55:04.997 --> 55:06.955
You want to be a good queen?

55:06.999 --> 55:08.827
Good queens actually listen.

55:08.870 --> 55:11.046
You know what I heard
back there?

55:11.090 --> 55:13.397
Differences do matter.

55:15.573 --> 55:18.227
Like-like you and me.

55:18.271 --> 55:20.839
We're too different
to get along.

55:20.882 --> 55:23.102
Just like all the other Trolls.

55:34.592 --> 55:37.072
-We arereally different.
-So different.

55:37.116 --> 55:38.378
-Completely out of harmony.
-Completely.

55:38.422 --> 55:39.858
I don't even know
why we're friends.

55:39.901 --> 55:42.208
Neither do I.

55:49.781 --> 55:51.870
So...

55:51.913 --> 55:56.309
why do I care about you more
than anybody else in the world?

56:00.008 --> 56:02.228
Weird, right?

56:05.100 --> 56:07.320
♪

56:13.326 --> 56:18.113
♪ I know your favorite song

56:18.157 --> 56:22.988
♪ I hear it every day

56:23.031 --> 56:27.514
♪ Whoever made your smile

56:27.558 --> 56:32.780
♪ Made it to get in my way

56:32.824 --> 56:37.263
♪ And every time you laugh

56:37.306 --> 56:42.224
♪ You make that little sound

56:42.268 --> 56:46.577
♪ It's just the hardest thing

56:46.620 --> 56:51.495
♪ To love you
but not know how ♪

56:51.538 --> 56:55.412
♪ I hate that you're perfect

56:56.369 --> 57:00.634
♪ You're perfect for me

57:02.810 --> 57:04.290
♪ What good are words

57:04.333 --> 57:10.209
♪ When they always
just get in our way? ♪

57:12.037 --> 57:13.734
♪ And it hurts the most

57:13.778 --> 57:19.174
♪ Just to know
that you don't feel the same ♪

57:19.218 --> 57:20.698
♪ The same

57:20.741 --> 57:22.700
♪ Yeah

57:22.743 --> 57:26.486
♪ And I hate
that you're perfect ♪

57:26.530 --> 57:27.487
[bell dings]

57:27.531 --> 57:31.273
♪ You're perfect for me

57:31.317 --> 57:32.623
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah♪

57:32.666 --> 57:36.104
♪ I hate that you're perfect

57:37.149 --> 57:43.111
♪ You're perfect for me.

57:43.155 --> 57:44.286
[quiet laugh nearby]

57:44.330 --> 57:45.200
BABY BUN [whispers]:
I see you, Branch.

57:45.244 --> 57:46.550
ARI [singsongy]:
Over here.

57:46.593 --> 57:47.420
-WANI: There he is.
-GOMDORI: Can you see me?

57:47.464 --> 57:48.508
-[gasps]
-[laughter]

57:48.552 --> 57:49.727
-[whistle]
-GOMDORI: I can see you.

57:49.770 --> 57:51.163
-BABY BUN: Let's get him.
-[laughter]

57:51.206 --> 57:52.512
WANI:
One, two, three.

57:52.556 --> 57:53.861
-ALL: Yay!
-[gasps, grunts]

57:53.905 --> 57:54.993
[yells]:
Oh!

57:55.036 --> 57:56.516
-[gasps]
-["Russian Roulette" playing]

57:56.560 --> 57:57.517
WANI:
Hey, crybaby.

57:57.561 --> 57:59.563
-Your name Poppy?
-[laughter]

57:59.606 --> 58:01.695
What? No.
Who are you guys?

58:01.739 --> 58:03.523
-We are the K-Pop Gang.
-[whoops]

58:03.567 --> 58:05.960
And you're going to take us
to Queen Poppy.

58:06.004 --> 58:06.961
[chuckles]:
What?

58:07.005 --> 58:09.224
["Mi Gente" playing]

58:10.922 --> 58:12.053
[music stops]

58:12.097 --> 58:13.881
-Not so fast, Tracy.
-[giggles]

58:13.925 --> 58:14.882
We're taking him.

58:14.926 --> 58:16.536
It's pronounced "Tresillo."

58:16.580 --> 58:18.669
-If you want him...
-[reggaeton beat plays]

58:18.712 --> 58:20.714
-you're going to have
to dance for him. -[laughter]

58:20.758 --> 58:23.848
I can't live in a world
without reggaeton.

58:23.891 --> 58:26.677
And we can't live in a world
without K-pop.

58:26.720 --> 58:29.114
-MALE VOICE: Dance-off!
-[dramatic music plays] -Ooh!

58:29.157 --> 58:32.378
["Russian Roulette" playing,
Trolls singing in Korean]

58:34.293 --> 58:35.250
♪ Heart-b-b-b-beat

58:35.294 --> 58:37.514
[singing in Korean]

58:39.994 --> 58:40.952
♪ Crazy

58:40.995 --> 58:42.214
[singing in Korean]

58:42.257 --> 58:44.303
♪ Russian roulette, b-b-beat.

58:44.346 --> 58:47.306
-["Mi Gente" playing,
singing in Spanish] -[gasps]

58:53.051 --> 58:54.618
♪ Freeze

58:54.661 --> 58:56.228
♪

58:56.271 --> 58:57.621
[screaming, laughing]

58:58.535 --> 59:01.276
♪ Un, dos, tres, leggo.

59:01.320 --> 59:02.277
[music stops]

59:02.321 --> 59:04.018
-Wow. -[giggles]
-Respect.

59:04.062 --> 59:05.498
-Respect.
-[grunts]

59:05.542 --> 59:07.326
-Why don't we split him?
-Huh?

59:07.369 --> 59:08.588
-Good idea. -Yeah.
-[laughter]

59:08.632 --> 59:10.938
Wait, wait, wait, wait,
wait, wait, wait.

59:10.982 --> 59:14.768
Why does Barb get to decide
which music gets to be saved?

59:14.812 --> 59:16.770
All music should be saved.

59:18.642 --> 59:21.558
All right, okay.
I'm listening, Pop Troll.

59:27.781 --> 59:31.176
FEMALE STRING VOICE:
♪ Oh, yeah.

59:32.003 --> 59:33.918
-[gasps]
-[panting]

59:33.961 --> 59:36.181
Poppy, there you are.

59:36.224 --> 59:39.619
Hickory!
Oh, it's so good to see you.

59:39.663 --> 59:40.881
Where's Branch?

59:40.925 --> 59:42.666
We had a fight.
He's gone.

59:42.709 --> 59:44.145
He's heading back
to Pop Village.

59:44.189 --> 59:46.104
[sighs] That's a shame.

59:46.147 --> 59:47.366
[Poppy sighs]

59:47.409 --> 59:49.542
I was so desperate
to be a good queen

59:49.586 --> 59:53.198
that I stopped listening
to anyone but myself.

59:54.678 --> 59:56.767
Including my best friend.
[sighs]

59:56.810 --> 59:59.900
And it's all because of
this stupid string.

59:59.944 --> 1:00:02.990
-[pop riff echoes]
-[magic jingling]

1:00:03.034 --> 1:00:05.993
Poppy, take the string
and run as fast as you can,

1:00:06.037 --> 1:00:07.081
-you hear me?
-What?

1:00:07.125 --> 1:00:08.343
What are you talking about?

1:00:08.387 --> 1:00:10.824
Trust me, just go.

1:00:10.868 --> 1:00:12.696
Now! Please! Just go!

1:00:12.739 --> 1:00:14.349
-[male voice grunting]
-Hickory, are you all right?

1:00:14.393 --> 1:00:15.960
-I'm fine.
-[male voice grumbling]

1:00:16.003 --> 1:00:17.265
Hey. Hey, now!

1:00:17.309 --> 1:00:18.266
Stop that!

1:00:18.310 --> 1:00:19.398
-[gasps]
-Here.

1:00:19.441 --> 1:00:21.269
-Oh, whoa, whoa!
-[male voice grunting]

1:00:22.096 --> 1:00:23.881
[Poppy shouts, gasps]

1:00:23.924 --> 1:00:26.013
-[grunts]
-[screams]

1:00:26.057 --> 1:00:27.972
-[grunts] Nein!
-[gasps]

1:00:28.015 --> 1:00:29.190
What are you doing, Hickory?!

1:00:29.234 --> 1:00:30.627
-Quiet, Dickory!
-POPPY: What's going on?

1:00:30.670 --> 1:00:33.542
-Hickory?
-I am so sorry.

1:00:33.586 --> 1:00:34.369
[yells]

1:00:34.413 --> 1:00:35.806
DICKORY:
Yeah.

1:00:35.849 --> 1:00:38.591
Show her who you really are,
Hickory!

1:00:42.595 --> 1:00:44.771
["Hocus Pocus" playing,
Dickory yodeling]

1:00:46.773 --> 1:00:48.775
[Hickory vocalizing]

1:00:52.126 --> 1:00:54.085
[sings high-pitched note]

1:00:54.128 --> 1:00:56.391
Wait.

1:00:56.435 --> 1:00:58.045
You're the Yodelers?

1:00:58.089 --> 1:00:59.046
[chuckles]:
Yeah.

1:00:59.090 --> 1:01:00.787
Ya darn skippy, playa-play.

1:01:00.831 --> 1:01:03.181
And you were gonna give
our string to Barb?

1:01:03.224 --> 1:01:07.228
Ding, ding. Give this person a
strudel for the correct answer.

1:01:07.272 --> 1:01:09.709
And you've been in back
the whole time?

1:01:10.579 --> 1:01:12.973
Next subject, please.

1:01:13.017 --> 1:01:14.845
Why would you do this?

1:01:15.715 --> 1:01:17.108
[German accent]:
So sorry.

1:01:17.151 --> 1:01:20.589
Uh, it was the only way to save
our beautiful yodeling.

1:01:20.633 --> 1:01:22.069
Hickory.

1:01:22.113 --> 1:01:24.419
But trust me, you need to get
out of here right away.

1:01:24.463 --> 1:01:25.725
What are you doing, Hickory?

1:01:25.769 --> 1:01:27.074
-Nein! -Dickory.
-[grunts]

1:01:27.118 --> 1:01:28.075
Shut your mouth-hole, please!

1:01:28.119 --> 1:01:29.903
-Let go!
-[grunting]

1:01:29.947 --> 1:01:31.688
-We must save yodeling!
-Stop it! -Got you!

1:01:31.731 --> 1:01:33.951
-[shouts]
-[laughs]

1:01:33.994 --> 1:01:37.389
-I thought I heard a yodel.
-[gasps] Queen Barb.

1:01:38.607 --> 1:01:40.827
-[pop riff plays]
-[Poppy gasps]

1:01:40.871 --> 1:01:42.611
The final notes of Pop.

1:01:42.655 --> 1:01:45.571
It will never invade
anyone's brain again.

1:01:45.614 --> 1:01:47.704
I'm not gonna let you do this!

1:01:52.839 --> 1:01:55.102
This is who I've been
worried about?

1:01:55.146 --> 1:01:56.930
This little pipsqueak?

1:01:56.974 --> 1:01:59.803
I'll never stop fighting
until I make things right.

1:01:59.846 --> 1:02:01.805
-And I'm not a pipsqueak!
-Uh, yeah, you are,

1:02:01.848 --> 1:02:03.763
'cause I'm, like, a whole
centimeter taller than you.

1:02:03.807 --> 1:02:05.547
No! [grunts]
Leave me alone!

1:02:05.591 --> 1:02:07.724
Leave you alone?
Uh, I'm sorry.

1:02:07.767 --> 1:02:10.291
You were the one who was all
desperate to be best friends.

1:02:10.335 --> 1:02:12.380
Get your hands off me.

1:02:12.424 --> 1:02:13.555
Oh, okay. All right.

1:02:13.599 --> 1:02:15.122
You're feisty.
I respect that.

1:02:15.166 --> 1:02:17.429
Strong woman to strong woman,
am I right?

1:02:17.472 --> 1:02:19.561
But you know
who else was feisty?

1:02:20.780 --> 1:02:22.739
Pop Village.

1:02:22.782 --> 1:02:24.175
[gasps]

1:02:24.218 --> 1:02:26.090
Oh, no. No!

1:02:27.134 --> 1:02:29.354
[panting]

1:02:30.355 --> 1:02:31.922
Everyone! Everyone!

1:02:31.965 --> 1:02:33.227
We're back!

1:02:33.271 --> 1:02:34.489
[gasps]

1:02:35.360 --> 1:02:37.754
[gasps] Oh, no.

1:02:40.844 --> 1:02:42.802
-Biggie! You won't believe it!
-Hello, Biggie.

1:02:42.846 --> 1:02:45.805
We were attacked
by Barb and her barbarians!

1:02:45.849 --> 1:02:48.199
She took everybody
to Volcano Rock City.

1:02:48.242 --> 1:02:49.548
It was scary.

1:02:49.591 --> 1:02:50.810
Rock me, Daddy.

1:02:50.854 --> 1:02:52.377
Mm, that's nice.

1:02:54.205 --> 1:02:56.773
♪

1:02:58.731 --> 1:03:01.516
I shouldn't have left her.

1:03:01.560 --> 1:03:03.301
She wouldn't have left me.

1:03:03.344 --> 1:03:05.651
Never, no matter
how scared she was.

1:03:06.565 --> 1:03:09.350
I've got to go back.

1:03:09.394 --> 1:03:11.918
We're coming with you, Biggie.

1:03:11.962 --> 1:03:14.529
We got to go save
our best friend.

1:03:14.573 --> 1:03:17.532
But how? We'll never
make it past security.

1:03:17.576 --> 1:03:19.839
We'll overpower them
with muscles!

1:03:19.883 --> 1:03:21.972
-[strains]
-[muscles squeak]

1:03:23.538 --> 1:03:26.324
Or... we could overpower them

1:03:26.367 --> 1:03:28.152
-with fashion.
-With fashion.

1:03:28.195 --> 1:03:30.589
♪

1:03:34.898 --> 1:03:36.377
Ouch.

1:03:36.421 --> 1:03:37.596
[whimpers]:
Oh.

1:03:39.206 --> 1:03:40.555
Ooh.

1:03:40.599 --> 1:03:42.383
[rock music playing]

1:03:42.427 --> 1:03:45.909
Rock and roll! [laughs]

1:03:57.311 --> 1:03:59.531
[crowd cheering]

1:04:00.924 --> 1:04:02.751
TROLL: All right,
where do we put these things?

1:04:02.795 --> 1:04:04.318
TROLL 2:
I need a circuit hookup.

1:04:04.362 --> 1:04:06.712
[quietly]: Okay, come on.
Let's go, let's go, let's go.

1:04:06.755 --> 1:04:10.107
[bells jingling quietly]

1:04:11.412 --> 1:04:13.893
Hey. Stop right there.

1:04:13.937 --> 1:04:15.286
[jingling stops]

1:04:15.329 --> 1:04:17.114
BIGGIE: Legsly, I told you
not to wear your anklet.

1:04:17.157 --> 1:04:20.073
Only Rock Trolls
are allowed back here.

1:04:20.117 --> 1:04:23.816
Well, it's funny
you should mention that,

1:04:23.860 --> 1:04:28.690
because we are genuine
Hard Rockers.

1:04:28.734 --> 1:04:30.997
[electric guitar strums weakly]

1:04:32.042 --> 1:04:33.478
[deep voice]:
One, two, three, four!

1:04:33.521 --> 1:04:34.914
-♪ Rainbows, unicorns
-[heavy metal music playing]

1:04:34.958 --> 1:04:36.611
♪ Everything nice, yeah

1:04:36.655 --> 1:04:38.265
♪ Sugarplums, fairy dust

1:04:38.309 --> 1:04:40.964
♪ Everything nice, yeah

1:04:41.007 --> 1:04:43.488
-♪ Brush your teeth.
-[hat squeaks]

1:04:44.881 --> 1:04:46.012
Cool.

1:04:46.056 --> 1:04:48.406
Hurry up.
The show's about to start, man.

1:04:48.449 --> 1:04:50.147
Queen Barb's
about to go onstage.

1:04:52.323 --> 1:04:53.585
We're screwed.

1:04:53.628 --> 1:04:55.848
-[rock music playing]
-[crowd cheering]

1:04:58.111 --> 1:04:59.591
BARB:
So, Popcorn,

1:04:59.634 --> 1:05:01.158
is being my best friend

1:05:01.201 --> 1:05:03.073
everything you could have
ever dreamed of?

1:05:03.116 --> 1:05:05.292
-[grunts]
-[Barb and Trolls laugh]

1:05:05.336 --> 1:05:06.903
I am not your best friend.

1:05:06.946 --> 1:05:09.688
You don't have to be
embarrassed. I get it.

1:05:09.731 --> 1:05:12.125
Being queen
can be kind of lonely.

1:05:12.169 --> 1:05:14.649
CROWD [chanting]:
Barb! Barb! Barb! Barb! Barb!

1:05:14.693 --> 1:05:17.043
[chanting fades]

1:05:17.087 --> 1:05:20.220
There's all this pressure
to be a great queen.

1:05:22.222 --> 1:05:24.703
And instead of real friends,
you're just surrounded by

1:05:24.746 --> 1:05:28.098
people who just tell you
what you want to hear.

1:05:29.360 --> 1:05:31.797
You know, other than
your terrible taste in music

1:05:31.840 --> 1:05:34.495
and clothing
and general lifestyle,

1:05:34.539 --> 1:05:36.889
you and me are the same,
Popsqueak.

1:05:36.933 --> 1:05:38.282
Uh... [scoffs]
No, we're not.

1:05:38.325 --> 1:05:40.849
We're both queens who just
want to unite the world.

1:05:40.893 --> 1:05:42.503
You don't want
to unite the world.

1:05:42.547 --> 1:05:44.027
You want to destroy it!

1:05:44.070 --> 1:05:45.506
Nuh-uh. No way.

1:05:45.550 --> 1:05:47.726
No. I don't know
who told you that.

1:05:47.769 --> 1:05:50.859
Music has done nothing
but divide us.

1:05:50.903 --> 1:05:52.992
Now that I have
the final string,

1:05:53.036 --> 1:05:57.214
I can make us all one nation
of Trolls, under rock.

1:05:57.257 --> 1:05:58.867
[guitar roars]

1:05:58.911 --> 1:06:01.044
[magic jingling, whooshing]

1:06:03.524 --> 1:06:05.135
[pop riff plays]

1:06:12.229 --> 1:06:14.361
[rock riff echoes]

1:06:14.405 --> 1:06:15.536
[laughs]

1:06:15.580 --> 1:06:16.973
What are you gonna do?

1:06:17.016 --> 1:06:19.584
Play the ultimate power chord,
and then...

1:06:19.627 --> 1:06:20.759
[chuckles]

1:06:20.802 --> 1:06:22.587
You'll see!

1:06:26.808 --> 1:06:28.810
-["Barracuda" playing]
-[crowd cheering]

1:06:33.990 --> 1:06:36.949
[crowd grunting in unison
to rhythm]

1:06:36.993 --> 1:06:40.039
-♪ Queen Barb!
-[crowd cheering]

1:06:40.083 --> 1:06:42.041
♪ So this ain't the end

1:06:42.085 --> 1:06:46.480
♪ I saw you again today

1:06:46.524 --> 1:06:49.657
♪ I had to turn my heart away

1:06:49.701 --> 1:06:51.616
[crowd grunting in unison
to rhythm]

1:06:51.659 --> 1:06:53.618
